#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:5
msgid "mmap_prepare callback HOWTO"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:8
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:10
msgid ""
"The ``struct file->f_op->mmap()`` callback has been deprecated as it is both "
"a stability and security risk, and doesn't always permit the merging of "
"adjacent mappings resulting in unnecessary memory fragmentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:14
msgid ""
"It has been replaced with the ``file->f_op->mmap_prepare()`` callback which "
"solves these problems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:17
msgid ""
"This hook is called right at the beginning of setting up the mapping, and "
"importantly it is invoked *before* any merging of adjacent mappings has "
"taken place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:21
msgid ""
"If an error arises upon mapping, it might arise after this callback has been "
"invoked, therefore it should be treated as effectively stateless."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:24
msgid ""
"That is - no resources should be allocated nor state updated to reflect that "
"a mapping has been established, as the mapping may either be merged, or fail "
"to be mapped after the callback is complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:29
msgid "Mapped callback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:31
msgid ""
"If resources need to be allocated per-mapping, or state such as a reference "
"count needs to be manipulated, this should be done using the ``vm_ops-"
">mapped`` hook, which itself should be set by the >mmap_prepare hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:35
msgid ""
"This callback is only invoked if a new mapping has been established and was "
"not merged with any other, and is invoked at a point where no error may "
"occur before the mapping is established."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:39
msgid ""
"You may return an error to the callback itself, which will cause the mapping "
"to become unmapped and an error returned to the mmap() caller. This is "
"useful if resources need to be allocated, and that allocation might fail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:44
msgid "How To Use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:46
msgid ""
"In your driver's struct file_operations struct, specify an ``mmap_prepare`` "
"callback rather than an ``mmap`` one, e.g. for ext4:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:56
msgid "This has a signature of ``int (*mmap_prepare)(struct vm_area_desc *)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:58
msgid "Examining the struct vm_area_desc type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:83
msgid ""
"This is straightforward - you have all the fields you need to set up the "
"mapping, and you can update the mutable and writable fields, for instance:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:106
msgid ""
"Importantly, you no longer have to dance around with reference counts or "
"locks when updating these fields - **you can simply go ahead and change "
"them**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:109
msgid "Everything is taken care of by the mapping code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:112
msgid "VMA Flags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:114
msgid ""
"Along with ``mmap_prepare``, VMA flags have undergone an overhaul. Where "
"before you would invoke one of vm_flags_init(), vm_flags_reset(), "
"vm_flags_set(), vm_flags_clear(), and vm_flags_mod() to modify flags (and to "
"have the locking done correctly for you, this is no longer necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:119
msgid ""
"Also, the legacy approach of specifying VMA flags via ``VM_READ``, "
"``VM_WRITE``, etc. - i.e. using a ``-VM_xxx``- macro has changed too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:122
msgid ""
"When implementing mmap_prepare(), reference flags by their bit number, "
"defined as a ``VMA_xxx_BIT`` macro, e.g. ``VMA_READ_BIT``, ``VMA_WRITE_BIT`` "
"etc., and use one of (where ``desc`` is a pointer to struct vm_area_desc):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:126
msgid ""
"``vma_desc_test_any(desc, ...)`` - Specify a comma-separated list of flags "
"you wish to test for (whether _any_ are set), e.g. - "
"``vma_desc_test_any( desc, VMA_WRITE_BIT, VMA_MAYWRITE_BIT)`` - returns "
"``true`` if either are set, otherwise ``false``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:130
msgid ""
"``vma_desc_set_flags(desc, ...)`` - Update the VMA descriptor flags to set "
"additional flags specified by a comma-separated list, e.g. - "
"``vma_desc_set_flags(desc, VMA_PFNMAP_BIT, VMA_IO_BIT)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:133
msgid ""
"``vma_desc_clear_flags(desc, ...)`` - Update the VMA descriptor flags to "
"clear flags specified by a comma-separated list, e.g. - "
"``vma_desc_clear_flags( desc, VMA_WRITE_BIT, VMA_MAYWRITE_BIT)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:138
msgid "Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:140
msgid ""
"You can now very easily have actions be performed upon a mapping once set up "
"by utilising simple helper functions invoked upon the struct vm_area_desc "
"pointer. These are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:144
msgid ""
"mmap_action_remap() - Remaps a range consisting only of PFNs for a specific "
"range starting a virtual address and PFN number of a set size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:147
msgid ""
"mmap_action_remap_full() - Same as mmap_action_remap(), only remaps the "
"entire mapping from ``start_pfn`` onward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:150
msgid ""
"mmap_action_ioremap() - Same as mmap_action_remap(), only performs an I/O "
"remap."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:153
msgid ""
"mmap_action_ioremap_full() - Same as mmap_action_ioremap(), only remaps the "
"entire mapping from ``start_pfn`` onward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:156
msgid ""
"mmap_action_simple_ioremap() - Sets up an I/O remap from a specified "
"physical address and over a specified length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:159
msgid ""
"mmap_action_map_kernel_pages() - Maps a specified array of `struct page` "
"pointers in the VMA from a specific offset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:162
msgid ""
"mmap_action_map_kernel_pages_full() - Maps a specified array of `struct "
"page` pointers over the entire VMA. The caller must ensure there are "
"sufficient entries in the page array to cover the entire range of the "
"described VMA."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/mmap_prepare.rst:167
msgid ""
"**NOTE:** The ``action`` field should never normally be manipulated "
"directly, rather you ought to use one of these helpers."
msgstr ""
